      "text": [
        ": سُئِلَ أَبُو إِبْرَاهِيمَ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اَلْمَرْأَةِ يَكُونُ لَهَا زَوْجٌ قَدْ أُصِيبَ فِي عَقْلِهِ بَعْدَ مَا تَزَوَّجَهَا أَوْ عَرَضَ لَهُ جُنُونٌ فَقَالَ \"لَهَا أَنْ تَنْزِعَ نَفْسَهَا مِنْهُ إِنْ شَاءَتْ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4818 - Al-Qasim ibn Muhammad Al-Jawhari narrated from Ali ibn Abi Hamzah who said: Abu Ibrahim (Imam Musa ibn Jafar Al-Kadhim (as)) was asked about a woman whose husband lost his sanity after marrying her or developed insanity.\nImam (as) said: \"She has the right to separate herself from him if she wishes.\""
        ]
      }
